Translation.Text: Start slow and raw tool path simulation now. Warning: This simulation is generic for all machines and post-processors. It is therefore very rough and can only act as a hint.

Load the CAM simulation file that was created during tool path calculation. Note: The precision of the simulation was configured during the original tool path calculation and depends on it's own post-processor simulation.
Do you also want to create milling simulation result? Warning: Simulation makes the tool path calculation process slower.
Do you want to keep the current stabilizer orientation?
A stabilizer was not created correctly and cannot be stored for CAM. Do you want to remove it from nesting?
Do you really want to destroy the transponder? The material blank cannot be milled again afterwards!
Move nesting objects by mouse Keyboard options: - Ctrl: Rotate

Add support pins by clicking on the reconstructions. Drag and drop to reposition. Click to apply new settings. Keyboard options: - Shift: Change docking position of existing support pin (and it's diameter) - Ctrl: Delete an existing support pin - Shift+Ctrl: Toggle automatic machine disconnection for the support pin.

Show window with all constructions ready for nesting. Tip: To import files to the nesting queue, you can drag/drop the files by mouse from explorer onto this button which adds them to the nesting queue.
Double-click the blank in the material library to load it!
No restorations in this blank that could be viewed
Save the current nesting into the library
Click to remove all designs from nesting. Right-click to remove the blank itself from nesting.
Successfully registered a new material blank!
Make sure to mark your physical material blank with it's blank ID:
'Mark as milled' is not possible with currently loaded blank. Please try again later when no blank is loaded into nesting that has same ID.
Given production code was already used. Please check your material blanks and try again.
A material blank which would match the information from the product code could not be found. Please create the material block manually.
Existing material blank with given product code will be loaded.
Warning: A problem occurred during tool path calculation. Production problems may occur.
Cancel production for this tool path file (recommended)
Continue production for this tool path file (dangerous)
Do you really want to revert the material blank to it's previous state?
The loaded blank has is of unknown type. The material blank library may be out of date, or this blank file may be too old. Please try to re-register its type (click 'Add blank')
The loaded blank is not compatible with the current machine any more. The material blank library may be out of date, or this blank file may be too old.
Note: Machine selection was automatically changed to {0}
The loaded blank is not compatible with any machine available in this installation.

Yes, unload blank but keep reconstructions.
No, do not change machine selection.
Note: Material blank slot name changed from {0} to {1}
Problem: Tool paths already exists for parts in the blank. What do you want to do?
Parts and their milled material will be removed from blanks
Treat parts as not milled and discard tool paths
Use this option if you plan to mill those parts in different holder or different machine.
Do not change machine, slot or holder configuration.
Error: Machine or material configuration problem!
Error: Nesting module is not activated on the dongle
This will cut out the material from the blank and remove the designs. Please make sure that the real blank is already milled at this position.
Only remove designs that have a calculated tool path.
The design is already in a CNC file. You can either delete the CNC file or cut out the design from the blank.
Is water cooling enabled on the machine?
What type of machine should be used?
Automatic rotation of nested parts to change the inclination inside the machine angle limits.
Automatically rotate nested parts to align it's milling axes to the 4th axis of the machine.
Nesting detected parts that were not saved. Do you really want to continue?
The selected machine is not configured for exocam. Tool path calculation is disabled and nesting does not know any machine limits. Please contact your software support to use the selected machine.
The selected machine is not installed with exocam tool path calculation. Please contact your software support to use the selected machine.
Warning: The original machine of the loaded scene file is not configured for this software. Please select the correct machine manually.
Nesting shows warning for unknown machines.
Click on support pin to apply new settings
Click on reconstruction to add support pin
Drag and drop restorations to position. Hold Ctrl to rotate.

Add external design files to the nesting queue. Tip: You can also drag/drop the files by mouse from explorer directly into the nesting 3D view to start the import.

Direct manual import of external design files to the nesting without using the nesting queue. Tip: You can also drag/drop the files by mouse from explorer directly into the nesting 3D view to start the import.
Import into nesting is not possible for any of the selected file types.
Problems occurred during import of external data for nesting. It is NOT recommended to mill the imported part. Continue at own risk!
Errors occurred during import of external data for nesting. Unfortunately, import is not possible for this dataset.

Do you really want to continue (not recommended)?
If activated, the software does not allow manual rotation of construction axes relatively to the limited axis of the machine.
Do you want to visualize undercuts for all nested constructions now? Hint: You can always refresh visualization of a construction using mouse context menu option 'Visualize Undercuts'
Accept and use all changes in current nesting.
Rotate around z-Axis by 180 deg. to improve size but keep 4-axis limits.

Please select the type of the designed reconstruction.

Do you want to accept the defined margin for the constructed design? Please note that this operation cannot be reverted, but the preparation margin and it's insertion direction can be corrected later.

Tip:
Next time when copying STL files, make sure to also include accompanying files in the same directory, such as:
*.constructionInfo, *.pol, *.asc, *.cam, *.xml
Everything you do in this wizard will then be performed automatically!
Set insertion direction using buttons below:
Set secondary direction using buttons below:

Not all design types were defined yet.
Note: Reconstruction cannot be imported to nesting when not all design types are defined.
Are you sure to discard all previous design information?
Margins can now be defined by mouse click.
Click on the margin you would like to modify or click 'Next step' when done.

Please define the insertion direction of construction.
Hints: 1. Insertion directions can be modified by dragging the arrows or using the three buttons below.
2. The green arrow marks the insertion direction, the blue one the z axis.
Secondary milling directions can be modified by dragging the arrows or using the three buttons below.

The material blank will now be marked as milled. Please make sure that your selection in the blank library represents the actual state of the production of the blank!
This state will be set as the current state for blank

The material blanks will now be marked as milled. Please make sure that your selection in the blank library represents the actual state of production of the blanks!
This state will be set as the current state for the following blanks:
The nesting library detected directories which contain no valid data for the nesting. Do you wish to delete the following directories?
Save the current nesting. Do not transfer nested parts to the new material blank.
Yes, and transfer newly nested parts.
Leave the current nesting unsaved and transfer nested parts to the new material blank.
The current nesting is not valid and cannot be saved.
All recent changes in current nesting will be lost.
Keep current nesting to fix it manually
Are you sure to reload the original blank shape? The history of milled areas of this blank will be lost!
Only one part is allowed to be nested in this kind of material blank.
Only single teeth are allowed to be nested in this kind of material blank.

Auto detection takes place during tool path calculation, so users can neither check, influence or change the automatically detected designs. Therefore, it is not recommended to use this feature.
If other files for this dataset are available (e.g. .constructionInfo, .asc/.pts/.xml or similar), place files in the same directory as the STL before loading it.
If no other files are available, it is recommended to manually define preparation margins and reconstruction types in this wizard.
Do you really want to use auto detection in CAM?
You need to define the implant geometry for the abutment before you can continue.
To add an implant to a tooth, click on it's preparation margin. Then, you have to define the lower implant geometry margin and then the upper screw channel margin.

Do you want to reset the default alignment of the imported data? Note that previous changes might get lost when you do this. Warning: Use this functionality only if imported data have not been aligned to z-axis by default.

Please define main axis of the data by viewing from top onto the design and pressing the button "Set from view".
Hints: 1. In most cases, the suggested default view (accessible by button "Default View") is fine.
2. In rare other cases, select the correct view button on top or rotate the view by mouse.

Verify that all margins are correct and that the screw channel direction was correctly set.
Click near a margin to edit it.
Click 'Next step' when all margins are OK.

Verify that all margin lines are correctly set.
To edit existing definitions, use the menu buttons below.
To add a margin to a bridge, click 'Add tooth to bridge'. Note that pontics don't need to be added, since there's no margin line to define.
The current screw channel axis seems to be angulated relatively to the implant axis!
Please define axis occlusal, i.e. the secondary insertion direction.

In the product code field, only codes without material blank infos are allowed. To create a material blank from code with blank information, please use the field left of the 'Generate' button.
